post_text:
The Greater Franklin Food Pantry is now located in the Franklin Railroad and Community Museum's Farmhouse Community Center at 574 Main Street, Franklin (same building as Franklin Eyewear LLC).
Join us for our first open hours at the new location THIS FRIDAY, 2pm – 4pm.

We are open to all Franklin and Treadwell residents who are in need of food. During your first visit we will ask that you complete a simple form, and then you are able to visit us, as needed, once per month.

At this time, customers are required to wear masks when inside the building. We also have hand sanitizer available upon entering.

Questions, comments, suggestions, and donations are welcome.
Call or text: 607-386-1601
GreaterFranklinFoodPantry.org
P.O. Box 209, 574 Main Street, Franklin, NY 13775
Current Hours: Fridays, 2pm – 4pm

Delaware County Summer Youth Employment
Are you between 14-20 and looking for a summer job? We have a program for you! Delaware County is currently accepting applications for youth ages 14-20 for the Summer Youth Employment Program. This program offers summer jobs and paid educational opportunities for kids right in their own communities. Your safety is important to us! Protective equipment and additional supervisory staff will be provided to keep everyone as safe as possible. Remember it’s the early birds that get the worms so apply today! Please call 607-832-5782 for your application to be emailed or mailed out.

post_text:
Hello Franklin Families!

We hope you are doing well. We can't tell you enough how much we miss all of you. In an effort to say a quick hello, we will be having a car parade on Friday, April 24th.
The faculty and Staff of Franklin will be driving through town and around the outskirts of town saying hello. Please join us by standing outside your house or meeting us at a site along the route in which your parents can park their car. Times are indicated on the route. Ouleout Golf Course has also offered a place for people to park if the car parade does not make it by your house.
Can't wait to see you all!

post_text:
Home instruction vocab word of the day: Equinox

What is an Equinox?

The Spring Equinox will be here tonight at 11:49 PM (US Eastern Time); the sun will be directly over the equator.

Equinoxes and solstices have inspired people's curiosity and helped them organize their lives since before history was recorded. Your students are likely no exception.

Here are some basic facts to share:

• Equinoxes occur twice each year, in March and September.

• On only those two days each year, all people on Earth experience an almost equal duration of daylight and nighttime. (Due to the size of the sun and refraction of light, day is actually eight minutes longer than night on the equinoxes.)

• Equinox is Latin for equal night.

• Equinoxes also mark the midpoint in the year between the Summer Solstice and Winter Solstice; the longest and shortest periods of daylight in a day.

Due to one confirmed COVID 19 case in a DCMO district, not Franklin, and several more individuals being tested in the county, FCS will not be able to have students report to school on Tuesday morning (3.17.20) as scheduled. We apologize for any inconvenience.

Faculty and staff will be on hand to distribute instructional materials from 10AM-12PM. Administration will distribute remaining materials from 1-4 PM and also by appointment on Wednesday.

A recorded call will go out at 5:45AM tomorrow morning. Sorry for the last minute change. All other DCMO districts who planned on having students attend on Tuesday have cancelled as well.

Please call our offices as needed. Thanks for your ongoing support and flexibility.
